    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm not sure. I think Solidity masks when storing the value in a uint8 variable. If you store the value using assembly, you're skipping the masking.\r\n\r\nI ran a quick test.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\n        uint8 v;\r\n        assembly {\r\n            v := 0x11111111111111111111111111111111\r\n        }\r\n        return v + 1;\r\n```\r\n\r\nThe addition was performed with an unmasked `v`.\r\n\r\nSolidity may mask at some later point, but it doesn't seem reliable at all.",
